## First-time setup

If you've landed in this repo without the boilerplate workspace set up,
several skills (cross-repo memory, identity-aware reports, brag log
accumulation) won't be available. The repo works standalone, but the full
experience requires the boilerplate.

To set up: clone the boilerplate source — for example, into
`~/<workspace>/source/claude_boilerplate/` — and run `/setup-workspace init`
from your chosen workspace folder. Register this project via `/hello` once
the workspace is ready.

## Memory

- `.claude/memory/MEMORY.md` — distilled patterns and decisions (committed).
- `.claude/memory/lessons-learned.md` — raw lessons inbox (committed).

Per-engineer state at the project root (`workstreams/`, `sessions/`, `collected/`, `artifacts/`, `contributions/`) is gitignored.

